# Changelog

## [61] latency-ux-optimizations — 2026-04-22

**Why:** Four compounding UX problems identified through live session testing: (1) 250ms of silence padded after every TTS audio chunk, multiplying with chunk count; (2) a "Thinking…" flash appeared between the connecting loader dismissing and the agent's opener playing — visible dead state; (3) the general agent creation wizard forced users to watch two sequential full-screen loaders (compile, then metrics) after submitting evaluation criteria; (4) `PlannerFlow` had dead branches for `'compiling'` and `'generating_metrics'` statuses that were never reachable after the wizard was restructured.

**What:** Removed the 250ms audio gap. Merged the agent-opener wait into the connecting loader so the session goes directly from loader to agent speaking with no intermediate state. Moved agent prompt compile to a background promise that starts as soon as the plan is ready — by the time the user submits evaluation criteria, compile is typically already done. Done screen now appears immediately after eval submit with muted progress steps that tick as each phase completes. `PlannerFlow` trimmed to only the three reachable statuses.

**Changes:**
- `src/hooks/useAgentSession.ts`: `awaitingOpenerRef` ref (boolean) set to `agentFirstSpeaker !== 'user'` before WebSocket creation; ArrayBuffer handler checks `awaitingOpenerRef.current` and calls `setPhase('active')` on first real audio chunk, clearing the ref; `session_ready` handler branches — user-first goes active immediately, agent-first stays in `'connecting'` with `sendAudioRef.current = false`; `audio_done` fallback: if `awaitingOpenerRef.current` still true (TTS failure), transitions to `'active'` anyway; audio enqueue: `nextPlayTimeRef.current = startAt + audioBuf.duration` — removed `+ 0.25` padding
- `src/pages/AgentLive.tsx`: connecting loader text changed from `"Connecting to {agentName}…"` to `"Starting your session…"` (covers both WS handshake and opener generation, avoids misleading agent-name display mid-loader)
- `src/components/agentspace/CreateAgentWizard.tsx`: `SavePhase` type (`'idle' | 'compile' | 'metrics' | 'save' | 'done'`) + `savePhase` state; `bgCompileRef` holds the in-flight compile promise; `planResultRef` stores plan for retry; `startBackgroundCompile(plan)` fires compile as a background IIFE when plan is ready, stores result in `finalSpec`/`configuredSpec`; `runPlanner` and `handleAnswersSubmitted` now call `startBackgroundCompile` instead of awaiting compile inline; `handleEvalSubmit` jumps to `step='done'` + `savePhase='compile'` immediately, then awaits `bgCompileRef.current` (likely already resolved), retries once on failure, then runs metrics and save sequentially; `DoneStep`: renders as soon as `step='done'` regardless of `savedAgent`; shows `stepStatus`-driven progress rows (pending/running/done icons) while `savePhase !== 'done'`; all action tiles, links, first-speaker toggle, and Done button are disabled/muted until `isReady`
- `src/components/agentspace/wizard/PlannerFlow.tsx`: `PlannerStatus` type reduced to `'planning' | 'awaiting_answers' | 'awaiting_evaluation'`; ThinkingPanel render branches for `'compiling'` and `'generating_metrics'` removed

---

## [60] qna-wizard-parallel-flow — 2026-04-22

**Why:** The QnA agent creation wizard had three compounding UX problems: (1) the question generation step was blocking — users stared at a spinner before reaching the evaluation input; (2) the behavior step (tone, feedback mode) was a separate screen, adding an unnecessary gate; (3) moving to question review immediately after resource submit meant questions and compile were sequential from the user's perspective. Additionally, a React state initialization bug caused the question bank to always appear empty when the review screen mounted while generation was still in flight.

**What:** Complete redesign of the QnA creation flow for maximum parallelism. Both question generation and agent prompt compile now fire simultaneously the moment the user submits the resource step. The user moves immediately to the evaluation criteria input while both tasks run in the background. Question review is the last user-facing step — by the time it's reached, both tasks are typically done. Tone and feedback mode inputs moved into the resource step, eliminating the separate behavior step entirely. Tone is now a 4-option chip selector (Friendly Tutor, Formal Examiner, Strict Evaluator, Neutral Interviewer) rather than a free-text field. The resource step is redesigned as a 2-column layout so all inputs fit on screen without scrolling. The question review mounting bug is fixed: `QnAQuestionReview` only mounts after `questionsReady === true`, so `useState` initializes with real data rather than an empty array that never updates.

**Changes:**
- `src/components/agentspace/wizard/QnAResourceStep.tsx`: Rewrote entirely — tone input replaced with 4 chip buttons in a 2×2 grid; feedback mode radio cards added inline; 2-column layout (description + file upload left, tone + feedback right); removed all blocking loader logic; `onGenerate` signature now passes `tone` and `feedbackMode`; `canSubmit` requires a tone chip to be selected
- `src/components/agentspace/wizard/QnABehaviorStep.tsx`: Deleted — fully absorbed into `QnAResourceStep`
- `src/components/agentspace/wizard/QnAQuestionReview.tsx`: Removed `isLoading` prop and loading guard — loading state is now managed at the wizard level to avoid the initialization bug; removed `Loader2` import
- `src/components/agentspace/wizard/CreateQnAAgentWizard.tsx`: Rewrote entirely — new step order: `language-voice → resource-upload → evaluation → question-review → done`; `handleGenerateAssessment` fires `startBackgroundCompile` and `startBackgroundQuestions` in parallel then immediately sets step to `'evaluation'`; `handleEvalSubmit` stores criteria in `evalCriteriaRef` and goes to `'question-review'`; question-review renders loading spinner inline while `!questionsReady`, and only mounts `QnAQuestionReview` when `questionsReady === true`; `handleQuestionBankReady` awaits compile, patches reviewed bank into spec, runs metrics generation and save sequentially; done step shows muted progress steps (`compile → metrics → save`) until `savePhase === 'done'`; `PLACEHOLDER_BANK` used for compile (LLM ignores the bank field, confirmed bank is patched in after review); `evalCriteriaRef` and `compileContextRef` bridge the question-review and save steps; error recovery returns to `'question-review'` with retry

---

## [59] session-recording-replay — 2026-04-22

**Why:** Sessions left no artifact beyond the transcript and evaluation report. There was no way for reviewers or participants to hear what was actually said — critical for QA, assessment review, and resolving disputes about session quality.

**What:** Added a "Play Recording" button to `RunDetailPanel` that opens a `RecordingPanel` slide-in. The panel fetches two presigned R2 URLs (agent audio + user audio), plays them simultaneously through hidden `<audio>` elements, and syncs a scrolling transcript to the current playback position. Both WAV files are constructed server-side with silence gaps so that when played together they interleave naturally with no overlap.

**Changes:**
- `src/lib/api.ts`: added `RecordingData` interface (`agent_audio_url`, `user_audio_url`, `manifest`, `duration_ms`); added `fetchRecording(accessToken, runId)` calling `GET /api/v1/recordings/:runId`
- `src/components/agentspace/RunDetailPanel.tsx`: added `fmtTime` helper; added `RecordingPanel` component — fetches recording on open, renders two hidden `<audio>` elements driven by a single play/pause button, seekable range input, and a manifest-driven transcript that dims inactive turns and auto-scrolls to the current one; added `recordingOpen` state; added "Play Recording" button row in the detail panel (mutually exclusive with transcript panel); added `RecordingPanel` in `AnimatePresence`

---

## [58] agent-first-speaker — 2026-04-22

**Why:** The `agent_first_speaker` backend flag required matching frontend changes: UI toggles to set the value at creation and in config views, correct API typings, and critically, a bug fix in the session hook — on `session_ready` the hook was unconditionally setting `agentState = 'listening'` which enabled `sendAudioRef` immediately. When the backend was streaming the agent's opener, the mic was already sending audio, creating a stale buffer that the STT loop consumed as a phantom first user turn.

**What:** Segmented "Agent first / Participant first" toggles added to all relevant wizard done-steps and configure-view headers. `useAgentSession` gains an `agentFirstSpeaker` option: when `'agent'`, `session_ready` sets `agentState = 'thinking'` and explicitly blocks `sendAudioRef`, so no mic audio is sent until the opener's `audio_done` arrives and the normal listening cycle resumes. `AgentPublicConfig` propagates the flag from the backend through to the hook.

**Changes:**
- `src/lib/api.ts`: `Agent` interface gains `agent_first_speaker: string`; `saveAgent`, `updateAgent`, `saveQnAAgent` payload types gain `agent_first_speaker?: string`; `AgentPublicConfig` gains `agent_first_speaker: string`
- `src/components/agentspace/CreateAgentWizard.tsx` (DoneStep): `firstSpeaker` state initialized from `savedAgent.agent_first_speaker`; "Who opens the session" tile with Agent/Participant segmented control inserted between the 2×2 grid and Done button; `handleFirstSpeakerToggle` fires `updateAgent` immediately; `MessageSquare` icon + `updateAgent` added to imports
- `src/components/agentspace/wizard/AgentConfigureView.tsx`: `agentFirstSpeaker?: string` prop; `firstSpeaker` local state; `handleFirstSpeakerChange` fires `updateAgent` and calls `onAgentUpdated` with updated value; desktop "Agent first / Participant first" segmented control added to header after language badge group; compact mobile version added to mobile row
- `src/components/agentspace/wizard/QnAConfigureView.tsx`: `firstSpeaker` state initialized from `agent.agent_first_speaker`; `handleFirstSpeakerChange` fires `updateAgent` and mutates `agent.agent_first_speaker` locally; desktop segmented control added to header after language badge + gear group; compact mobile version added to mobile row alongside Voice button
- `src/components/agentspace/wizard/CreateQnAAgentWizard.tsx` (DoneStep): same "Who opens the session" tile as general wizard; `firstSpeaker` state + `handleFirstSpeakerToggle`; `MessageSquare` and `updateAgent` added to imports
- `src/hooks/useAgentSession.ts`: `agentFirstSpeaker?: string` option added; `session_ready` handler branches on value — when `'user'` keeps existing `setAgentState('listening')` behavior; when `'agent'` (default) explicitly sets `sendAudioRef.current = false` and `setAgentState('thinking')` so the `sendAudioRef` effect cannot re-enable sending until `audio_done` transitions back to `'listening'`
- `src/pages/AgentLive.tsx`: `agentFirstSpeaker: string` prop on `ActiveSession`; threaded from `config.agent_first_speaker ?? 'agent'` to `useAgentSession`

---

## [57] live-session-ux-improvements — 2026-04-22

**Why:** Two UX issues with the live session interface: (1) Incoming agent text appeared all at once with an awkward shadow/opacity transition effect that felt jarring during voice sessions. (2) There was a brief audible silence between consecutive TTS audio chunks due to no inter-chunk scheduling gap.

**What:** Transcript agent bubbles now use a `WordRevealText` component that reveals text one word at a time at 120ms intervals, matching roughly the expected speech rate. All Framer Motion animations and opacity classes removed from transcript bubbles — plain divs throughout. TTS scheduling adds a 250ms buffer after each chunk so consecutive audio plays gaplessly.

**Changes:**
- `src/components/agentlive/TranscriptPanel.tsx`: removed all `motion.div` / `AnimatePresence` wrappers from transcript entries and bubbles; added `WordRevealText` component — splits text on spaces, uses `wordPosRef` ref + `setInterval` at 120ms to reveal one word at a time, resets on `text` prop change; `WordRevealText` applied to the streaming agent text bubble; removed opacity and shadow conditional classes from partial/streaming bubbles
- `src/hooks/useAgentSession.ts`: `enqueueAudio` changed `nextPlayTimeRef.current = startAt + audioBuf.duration` to `startAt + audioBuf.duration + 0.25` — adds 250ms scheduling gap between queued audio buffers, eliminating the silent gap artifact

---

## [56] qna-resource-pdf-extraction-and-image-vision — 2026-04-21

**Why:** The QnA resource upload was base64-encoding raw PDF binaries and sending them as `[PDF_BASE64:...]` strings — useless for the LLM and catastrophic for token limits on scanned PDFs (2.4 MB → 606K tokens → 429 rate limit error). The upload also only supported PDF and .txt, with no way to attach image-based reference material.

**What:** PDF files are now processed with `pdfjs-dist` to extract their text layer before sending. Scanned/image-only PDFs (no text layer) fall back to rendering the first 1–3 pages as JPEG canvas snapshots, which are passed to the backend as vision content. Direct image upload (JPG/PNG/WebP) is also added with a 2 MB cap. Images — whether uploaded directly or rendered from a scanned PDF — are sent as base64 data URIs to the backend and forwarded to the LLM as vision content.

**Changes:**
- `package.json`: added `pdfjs-dist` dependency
- `src/components/agentspace/wizard/QnAResourceStep.tsx`:
  - `AttachedFile` interface gains `fileType: 'text' | 'image' | 'scanned-pdf'` and `pageImages?: string[]`
  - `arrayBufferToBase64` kept for image encoding
  - `extractPdfText` replaced by `extractPdfContent` — extracts text across all pages; if empty (scanned), renders pages 1–min(3, n) to canvas at scale 1.0 / JPEG 0.7 and returns `pageImages`
  - `handleFiles` now accepts JPG/PNG/WebP (2 MB cap); scanned PDFs count as one image slot (max 2 image slots total); image slot limit checked inline per file
  - `handleSubmit` builds `resourceImages` by merging direct image `dataUri` values and scanned PDF `pageImages`
  - `onGenerate` prop gains third arg `resourceImages: string[]`
  - File list shows `Image` icon for images and scanned PDFs; scanned PDFs show a `"Np scanned"` label
  - Upload zone hint updated to mention image formats
- `src/components/agentspace/wizard/CreateQnAAgentWizard.tsx`: `handleGenerateQuestions` signature gains `resourceImages: string[]`; passes `resource_images` to `generateQnAQuestions`
- `src/lib/api.ts`: `generateQnAQuestions` payload type gains `resource_images?: string[]`

---

## [55] agent-session-complete-signal — 2026-04-21

**Why:** After an agent delivered its closing statement the session stayed open indefinitely — the WebSocket kept waiting for user audio with no UI transition. The user had no indication the session was over unless they manually pressed End Session.

**What:** Frontend now handles a new `session_complete` message sent by the backend when the agent calls the `signal_session_complete` tool. On receipt, the mic is torn down (same path as manual `endSession()`) and the phase transitions to `'reporting'`, showing the report-loading UI while the evaluation runs. The WebSocket stays open to receive `session_report` as before.

**Changes:**
- `src/hooks/useAgentSession.ts`: added `case 'session_complete'` to the `ws.onmessage` switch — disconnects processor, stops mic stream, closes mic AudioContext, sets `sendAudioRef.current = false`, calls `setMicEnabled(false)`, transitions phase to `'reporting'`

---

## [54] agent-config-ui-ux-overhaul — 2026-04-21

**Why:** The agent configure pages (General and QnA) had accumulated several UX inconsistencies and layout issues: AI helper boxes cluttered every section with "Describe the change" popups that weren't needed; the metrics section had no visible constraint (users could add unlimited metrics despite a 4-slot backend limit); the voice/language picker was an inline expandable panel that pushed content down awkwardly; the Session/Evaluation tabs had mismatched save button placement; and the QnA config page diverged significantly from the General agent layout with no voice/language support, a centralized questions view, and underline tabs instead of pills.

**What:** A comprehensive redesign of both agent configure views. All AI helper boxes and Sparkles buttons removed. Metrics rebuilt as 4 fixed editable slots with color-coding for original vs. changed values and a live counter badge. Voice/language picker extracted into a reusable centered modal accessible from a gear icon in the header. Headers consolidated into a single sticky row with title, pill tabs, language badge, settings, and save. Evaluation tab switched to a 2-column layout (eval prompt main + metrics sidebar). QnA config aligned to match General Agent: pill tabs, voice/language modal, 2-column Profile tab with collapsible sections, compact scrollable Questions tab, and matching Evaluation layout.

**Changes:**
- `src/components/agentspace/wizard/VoiceSettingsModal.tsx` — **new**: reusable centered modal for voice & language selection; dark backdrop + blur, language dropdown, voice cards grid with gender badges and preview buttons, Cancel/Update Voice footer; uses framer-motion AnimatePresence for enter/exit animations
- `src/pages/AgentSpace.tsx` — live link copy button: `text-emerald-500` when agent is `live`, `text-gray-300` when `idle`; test link copy button: `text-orange-400` always; applied to both mobile cards and desktop rows
- `src/components/agentspace/wizard/AgentConfigureView.tsx` — **header**: title + pill tabs (Session / Evaluation) + language badge (`text-[10px] uppercase indigo-700 bg-indigo-50`) + settings gear icon (opens VoiceSettingsModal) + Save Changes button, all in one sticky row; mobile secondary row shows voice name + language + Voice button
- `src/components/agentspace/wizard/AgentConfigureView.tsx` — **voice**: removed inline `VoiceBar` component entirely; voice/language now changed via `VoiceSettingsModal` triggered from header gear icon
- `src/components/agentspace/wizard/AgentConfigureView.tsx` — **AI helpers removed**: subtitle "Edit sections directly or use AI..." removed; `EvalAiButton` component removed; `AiButton` component removed; `SectionHeader` simplified to plain label; all `onAiRewrite` prop plumbing removed from `StringSection`, `DictSection`, `CollapsibleSection`
- `src/components/agentspace/wizard/AgentConfigureView.tsx` — **metrics redesign**: 4 editable `<input>` slots in a grid; original metrics (from `initialMetrics`) render with mild gray styling (`bg-gray-50 border-gray-200 text-gray-600`); new/changed metrics render with soft indigo accent (`bg-indigo-50 border-indigo-100 text-indigo-700`); counter badge `X/4` in header turns emerald when full; empty slots show `+` placeholder; "Maximum 4 metrics reached" text removed
- `src/components/agentspace/wizard/AgentConfigureView.tsx` — **evaluation layout**: switched from single-column to 2-column on `md+` screens; left column (flex-1, order-2 on md) holds Eval Prompt textarea (rows=10); right column (w-[280px] sidebar, order-1 on md) holds the 4 metric slots
- `src/components/agentspace/wizard/AgentConfigureView.tsx` — **save consistency**: single Save Changes button in header works for both Session and Evaluation tabs; Evaluation tab exposes `save()` via `useImperativeHandle` so the parent can call it; per-tab save states (`sessionSaving`/`sessionSaved`/`evalSaving`/`evalSaved`) drive button copy (Saving…/Saved/Save Changes)
- `src/components/agentspace/wizard/QnAConfigureView.tsx` — **header**: redesigned to match General Agent — title + pill tabs (Profile / Questions / Evaluation) + language badge + gear icon + Save Changes button in one sticky row; underline tabs replaced with pill tabs in `bg-gray-100` container
- `src/components/agentspace/wizard/QnAConfigureView.tsx` — **tab order**: changed from `Questions | Profile | Evaluation` to `Profile | Questions | Evaluation`
- `src/components/agentspace/wizard/QnAConfigureView.tsx` — **voice/language added**: `VoiceSettingsModal` wired in; `agent.agent_language` and `agent.agent_voice` now displayed and editable (previously ignored despite being present on the `Agent` type); mobile secondary row with voice info + Voice button
- `src/components/agentspace/wizard/QnAConfigureView.tsx` — **AI helpers removed**: `AiRewritePopup` component removed; `SectionAiButton` component removed; "Regenerate Evaluation" block with Sparkles Generate button removed; all AI rewrite state and API calls (`handleRewrite`, `handleGenerateEval`) removed
- `src/components/agentspace/wizard/QnAConfigureView.tsx` — **profile layout**: switched from single-column stacked cards to 2-column `md:flex-row` layout matching General Agent's Session tab; left column (55%) holds Identity & Persona + Session Brief; right column holds Behavior Rules + Guardrails as collapsible cards with `ChevronDown` animation via `AnimatePresence`
- `src/components/agentspace/wizard/QnAConfigureView.tsx` — **questions compactness**: question items use `truncate` on display text, `rows=1` when editing, and tighter padding (`py-2` instead of `py-2.5`); both Fixed and Randomized columns are scrollable (`max-h-[360px] overflow-y-auto`); layout changed from centered (`max-w-4xl mx-auto`) to full-width (`px-5 py-5`)
- `src/components/agentspace/wizard/QnAConfigureView.tsx` — **evaluation layout**: switched to 2-column on `md+` matching General Agent; left column holds Eval Prompt textarea; right sidebar (w-[280px]) holds 4 metric slots with same original-vs-new color coding
- `src/components/agentspace/wizard/QnAConfigureView.tsx` — **save consistency**: single Save Changes button in header works for all three tabs (Questions/Profile/Evaluation); `handleHeaderSave` dispatches to the correct save handler per active tab

