## [53] trial-gating-and-balance-visibility — 2026-04-21

**Why:** Two UX gaps after the payment flow launched: (1) The Trial card was still shown as a "Downgrade" option to users who had already used a trial and then upgraded — the frontend was checking only the *current* subscription tier, missing the upgrade-from-trial case. (2) The token balance ring gauge and credit count in the header remained visible even when a subscription was cancelled or expired, showing stale data against a plan with no access.

**What:** Trial card is now filtered using a `had_trial` boolean returned by the backend (which checks both the current subscription row and `subscription_event` history). Balance bar is hidden when the subscription is not active via a new `subscriptionActive` field in `TokenContext`.

**Changes:**
- `src/lib/api.ts`: added `had_trial: boolean` to `AgentspaceSubscription` interface
- `src/context/TokenContext.tsx`: added `subscriptionActive: boolean` to context interface, default, and provider value (`subscription?.status === 'active'`)
- `src/components/agentspace/TokenBalanceBar.tsx`: returns `null` when `!subscriptionActive`, hiding the gauge for cancelled/expired plans
- `src/components/agentspace/PlanPanel.tsx`: trial filter now uses `subscription.had_trial` instead of `subscription.plan_tier === 'trial'` — correctly hides trial after upgrade
- `src/components/agentspace/NoActivePlanScreen.tsx`: same `subscription?.had_trial` filter applied to the plan grid

---

## [52] payment-flow-fixes — 2026-04-21

**Why:** Several rough edges after initial payment launch: `BillingPanel` crashed on open due to a leftover `setError` call. Expired/cancelled plans showed only a single locked "Renew Plan" button instead of the full plan picker. The payment confirmation page timed out after 30 seconds, which was too short for Razorpay webhook delivery in some regions.

**What:** `BillingPanel` crash fixed. Expired/cancelled plan state now falls through to the full plan grid with an expiry banner — users can pick any tier. `PlanPanel` adds "Get [Plan]" buttons for all tiers when the subscription is expired/cancelled. `PaymentSuccess` polling window extended to ~2 minutes.

**Changes:**
- `src/components/agentspace/BillingPanel.tsx`: removed stale `setError(null)` call that referenced an undefined setter — caused a crash on panel open
- `src/components/agentspace/NoActivePlanScreen.tsx`: removed the dedicated expired-plan screen that only showed a single "Renew Plan" button; expired state now renders the full plan grid with heading "Your plan has ended" and expiry date subtext
- `src/components/agentspace/PlanPanel.tsx`: removed single "Renew Plan" button from the current plan card; added `canRenew` condition in the all-plans grid that shows "Get [Plan]" buttons for all self-serve tiers when the subscription is expired or cancelled
- `src/pages/PaymentSuccess.tsx`: polling increased from 15 × 2s (30s) to 45 × 3s (~2 min); loading copy updated to "This can take up to a minute. Please don't close this page."

---

## [51] all-plans-self-serve — 2026-04-21

**Why:** Growth and Pro plans were gated behind "Talk to us" even though the Razorpay subscription flow was already in place for Trial/Starter. This blocked users from self-upgrading to higher tiers without a sales touch.

**What:** All four plan tiers are now purchasable directly via Razorpay checkout. The "Talk to us" CTA is removed from PlanPanel and replaced with "Get [Plan]" / "Upgrade now" / "Downgrade now" buttons for Growth and Pro cards.

**Changes:**
- `src/components/agentspace/PlanPanel.tsx`: `SELF_SERVE_TIERS` expanded from `{trial, starter}` to `{trial, starter, growth, pro}`; removed dead "Talk to us" fallback link from plan cards
- `src/components/agentspace/NoActivePlanScreen.tsx`: `SELF_SERVE_TIERS` expanded to all four tiers — Growth/Pro cards now render "Get Growth" / "Get Pro" pay buttons instead of mailto links

---

## [50] settings-restructure-plan-actions-billing — 2026-04-21

**Why:** The single `AgentSpaceSettingsPanel` with People/Plan tabs was hard to navigate and mixed member management with billing. Plan actions (switch, cancel) and a payment history view had no home. The settings entry point was a single "Settings" dropdown item instead of direct-access links.

**What:** `AgentSpaceSettingsPanel` is deleted and replaced by four focused slide-in panels (`MembersPanel`, `InvitesPanel`, `PlanPanel`, `BillingPanel`) accessible individually from the user dropdown. `PlanPanel` adds switch-plan (immediate Razorpay checkout or schedule-at-renewal) and cancel-subscription (now or at renewal) actions with inline confirm toggles. `BillingPanel` surfaces paginated `payment_transaction` history. A shared `SlidePanel` shell handles the slide-from-right animation and backdrop. `AgentSpaceHeader` replaces the single Settings button with four admin-only items.

**Changes:**
- `src/components/agentspace/SlidePanel.tsx` — new: shared backdrop + slide-from-right panel shell; props `open`, `onClose`, `title`, `subtitle?`, `children`; uses `AnimatePresence` + `motion.div` with `initial={{ x: '100%' }}`
- `src/components/agentspace/MembersPanel.tsx` — new: member list with role dropdown and remove action; extracted from `AgentSpaceSettingsPanel`
- `src/components/agentspace/InvitesPanel.tsx` — new: invite form + pending invite list with revoke; extracted from `AgentSpaceSettingsPanel`
- `src/components/agentspace/PlanPanel.tsx` — new: current plan card (status, period dates, cancel-at-renewal badge, used/remaining stats), cancel section with inline confirm toggle ("Cancel now" / "Cancel at renewal"), all-plans grid with switch buttons ("Upgrade/Downgrade now" + "At renewal") for non-current self-serve tiers, renew button for expired/cancelled subs, top-10 token history with test-session badge; no pagination
- `src/components/agentspace/BillingPanel.tsx` — new: paginated `payment_transaction` list (10/page); shows date, event label (Activated/Renewed/Cancelled/Failed), plan tier, amount (₹), status badge; fetch errors treated as empty state
- `src/components/agentspace/AgentSpaceHeader.tsx`: removed `onSettingsClick`; added `onMembersClick`, `onInvitesClick`, `onPlanClick`, `onBillingClick` props; replaced single Settings button with four admin-only dropdown items (Members/Users, Invites/UserPlus, Plan/CreditCard, Billing/Receipt); `TokenBalanceBar` wrapped in `hidden sm:block` to prevent mobile overflow; removed `overflow-hidden` from right-section container to allow dropdown positioning
- `src/components/agentspace/AgentSpaceSettingsPanel.tsx` — deleted (all content moved to the four panels above)
- `src/pages/AgentSpace.tsx`: replaced `settingsOpen` state with `membersOpen`, `invitesOpen`, `planOpen`, `billingOpen`; wired all four panels into render; all three `AgentSpaceHeader` render sites updated with new props
- `src/lib/api.ts`: added `cancel_at_period_end?: boolean` to `AgentspaceSubscription` interface; added `cancelSubscription(token, {agentspace_id, at_period_end})`, `switchPlan(token, {agentspace_id, new_plan_tier, at_period_end})`, `fetchPaymentTransactions(token, agentspace_id, page, page_size)`; added `PaymentTransaction` interface `{id, created_at, event_type, plan_tier, currency, amount_paid, status}`

