## [49] razorpay-only-payment-flow — 2026-04-21

**Why:** Stripe India moved to invite-only and blocks individual accounts from accepting payments in test mode. All payment flows route through Razorpay, which handles INR and currency conversion natively. The currency/region toggles in the UI added confusion without providing value.

**What:** Currency and region toggles removed from all three plan-selection surfaces. All payment calls hardcode `currency: "INR"`. Stripe checkout path remains gated behind `STRIPE_ENABLED=true` for future re-enablement.

**Changes:**
- `src/components/agentspace/NoActivePlanScreen.tsx`: removed `currency` state, `plansIntl` state and `getAllPlansIntl()` fetch, `India (₹) / Intl ($)` segmented toggle, Stripe checkout branch; `initiatePayment` always called with `currency: "INR"`
- `src/components/agentspace/AgentSpaceSettingsPanel.tsx`: removed `planCurrency` state, `allPlansIntl` state and `getAllPlansIntl()` fetch, `₹ INR / $ Intl` toggle in All Plans section, Stripe checkout branch in `handleRenewClick`; plan grid sourced from `allPlansIn` only
- `src/sections/Pricing.tsx`: removed `region` state, `Region` type, `plansIntl` state and `getAllPlansIntl()` fetch, `India (₹) / International ($)` toggle; plan cards sourced from `plansIn` only

---

## [48] self-serve-payments — 2026-04-21

**Why:** Subscriptions were activated manually by admins via an internal API call. Users had no way to purchase or renew a plan without a human in the loop. Trial and Starter plans needed a self-serve checkout flow (Razorpay INR recurring + Stripe USD) with automatic activation on webhook confirmation.

**What:** End-to-end recurring subscription purchase flow added for Trial and Starter plans. Frontend initiates a payment intent via a new `POST /api/v1/payments/initiate` endpoint, opens the Razorpay modal (or redirects to Stripe Checkout for USD), and polls `GET /api/v1/payments/status` on a new `/payment/success` page until the webhook-triggered activation lands. Activation is handled exclusively by gateway webhooks (`subscription.charged` for Razorpay, `checkout.session.completed` for Stripe) via an internal helper that replicates the admin activation logic. A renew button is surfaced in `AgentSpaceSettingsPanel` for expired/cancelled subs. Overage events are emitted to Stripe Meters for Growth/Pro USD workspaces at session end.

**Changes:**
- `src/lib/razorpay.ts` — new: `loadRazorpayScript()` idempotent script loader; `RazorpayOptions` and `RazorpayInstance` interfaces; `Window.Razorpay` global declaration
- `src/lib/api.ts`: added `RazorpayCheckoutData`, `StripeCheckoutData`, `CheckoutData` union, `PaymentStatusResponse` types; added `initiatePayment(token, {agentspace_id, plan_tier, currency})` and `fetchPaymentStatus(token, provider, ref)`
- `src/pages/PaymentSuccess.tsx` — new: polls `fetchPaymentStatus` every 2s up to 15 attempts; renders loading spinner → success card (plan name + "Go to Workspace") → timeout error card with support mailto
- `src/App.tsx`: added `<Route path="/payment/success" element={<PaymentSuccess />} />`
- `src/components/agentspace/NoActivePlanScreen.tsx`: Trial/Starter CTA buttons wired to `handlePayClick` — opens Razorpay modal (INR) or redirects Stripe (USD); Growth/Pro remain mailto; loading state per tier; error banner below grid
- `src/sections/Pricing.tsx`: Trial/Starter CTAs navigate to `/agent-space` (authenticated) or `/auth` (unauthenticated) instead of opening a modal
- `src/components/agentspace/AgentSpaceSettingsPanel.tsx`: added renew button for expired/cancelled subs in Plan tab; trial-expired renews as Starter; same `handleRenewClick` Razorpay pattern

