## [41] minor-fixes — 2026-04-14

**Why:** Three small issues: (1) HowItWorks Step 6 (Report) had no dwell time — the sticky scroll zone height only covered 5 transitions, so reaching the last step immediately scrolled the user past it with no time to read. (2) QnA agent file uploads silently failed for PDFs larger than ~500 KB — `btoa(String.fromCharCode(...new Uint8Array(buf)))` spread the entire buffer as function arguments, exceeding the JS call stack limit; the unhandled rejection meant `setFiles` was never called and uploaded files never appeared, with no error shown. (3) READMEs predated the QnA agent type and were missing the new wizard components and endpoints.

**What:** HowItWorks scroll zone now uses `STEPS.length` (not `STEPS.length - 1`) so Step 6 gets a full 600px of dwell. QnA upload now uses a chunked base64 helper (8 192-byte slices) that avoids the stack limit for any file size; the loop is wrapped in try/catch to show a user-visible error on failure, and the input resets after each selection so the same file can be retried. `frontend/README.md` updated with QnA agent type table and wizard component tree.

**Changes:**
- `src/sections/HowItWorks.tsx`: scroll zone height changed from `(STEPS.length - 1) * SCROLL_STEP` to `STEPS.length * SCROLL_STEP`
- `src/components/agentspace/wizard/QnAResourceStep.tsx`: added `arrayBufferToBase64()` helper using 8 192-byte chunked loop; replaced inline `btoa(String.fromCharCode(...))` spread with helper call; wrapped file-processing loop in try/catch with `setFileError('Could not read file. Please try again.')`; added `e.target.value = ''` reset in `onChange` handler
- `README.md`: added Agent Types table (General vs QnA); expanded project structure to list QnA wizard components (`CreateQnAAgentWizard`, `QnAResourceStep`, `QnAQuestionReview`, `QnABehaviorStep`, `QnAConfigureView`)

