## [20] profile-load-sequencing — 2026-03-06

**Why:** After clearing all DB rows, two concurrent calls to `GET /api/v1/profile/me` (React StrictMode double-fires effects) raced to create both the profile and the agentspace. The agentspace fetch in `AgentSpaceContext` fired before the profile creation finished — since profile creation is also what triggers default agentspace creation, the fetch returned an empty list and the UI showed a spinner indefinitely. Additionally, if profile creation failed entirely, the agentspace fetch would still proceed with a null profile.

**What:** Added a `!profile` guard to `loadSpaces` so the agentspace fetch only fires once both `profileLoading === false` and `profile !== null`. Added `profile` to the `useCallback` dependency array so the fetch re-triggers as soon as the profile becomes available.

**Changes:**
- `src/context/AgentSpaceContext.tsx` — `loadSpaces` bails early if `profileLoading || !profile` (was `profileLoading` only); `profile` added to the `useCallback` dependency array alongside `session?.access_token` and `profileLoading`; ensures agentspace fetch never fires while profile is still being created, preventing a race between default agentspace creation and the spaces list fetch

