## [14] session-reporting-flow — 2026-03-02

**Why:** Four related problems needed fixing together: (1) The frontend closed the WebSocket immediately after `endSession()`, so the `session_report` message (sent by the backend after generating the evaluation) could never be received — the frontend polled a REST endpoint instead, which consistently returned 404 before generation finished. (2) Certain audio chunks from Inworld TTS had odd byte lengths, crashing `Int16Array` with `RangeError: byte length of Int16Array should be a multiple of 2`. (3) After session end, the UX was a jarring dark loading screen followed by an abrupt jump to `ReportScreen` — the design should show `EndedScreen` immediately, with a live spinner while the report generates and a "View Report" button once it arrives. (4) The error page used a `🔒` emoji which broke the UI design system, and the agent configure view had no way to edit evaluation metrics post-creation.

**What:** Added a `'reporting'` WebSocket phase to the session hook that keeps the connection open while the backend generates the report. Redesigned post-session page flow so `EndedScreen` appears instantly after call end. Fixed Int16Array crash. Replaced emoji with Lucide icon. Added Session/Evaluation tabs to the agent configure view with a full AI-powered metric editor.

**Changes:**
- `src/hooks/useAgentSession.ts` — added `'reporting'` to `SessionPhase` type; added `SessionReport` interface (`report: EvaluationReport | null`, `runId: string | null`) and `sessionReport` state; `endSession()` now stops mic + mic AudioContext only (WS stays open), sends `{"type":"end_session"}`, and sets phase to `'reporting'`; added `case 'session_report'` in WS message handler: sets `sessionReport`, transitions phase to `'ended'`, calls `cleanup()`; added safety `useEffect` — if phase stays `'reporting'` for >25s, force-transitions to `'ended'` (guards against backend failure); fixed `enqueueAudio()`: trims trailing odd byte from `rawBuffer` before `new Int16Array(buf)` to prevent `RangeError`; fixed `ws.onclose` handler: uses functional `setPhase` update so it reads the current phase correctly and doesn't reset a cleanly-ended session back to `'ended'` via incorrect branching
- `src/pages/AgentLive.tsx` — `ActiveSession` now renders `EndedScreen` (with `isGeneratingReport`) during the `'reporting'` phase instead of a dark full-screen spinner, so the session-ended card appears the moment the user hangs up; replaced `<span className="text-2xl">🔒</span>` with `<Lock className="w-6 h-6 text-gray-500" />` (lucide-react) on the error state; removed `'report-loading'` page state entirely; added `'report'` page state that renders `ReportScreen`; `handleEnded(turnCount, report)`: if `report.report` has `scoring` data → `setReportData(report.report)` and go to `'ended'`; if graceful end but no scoring (no evaluation configured) → go to `'ended'` directly; if `report === null` (abrupt disconnect) → set `isPollingReport = true` and go to `'ended'`; fallback poll `useEffect` runs only when `isPollingReport && pageState === 'ended'` — calls `fetchLatestRunRecord` up to 2 times with 3s gap, sets `reportData` if a scored record is found, always clears `isPollingReport` when done; `EndedScreen` receives `isGeneratingReport={isPollingReport}`, `reportAvailable={!!reportData}`, `onViewReport={() => setPageState('report')}`; `ReportScreen` rendered at `'report'` page state
- `src/components/agentlive/EndedScreen.tsx` — added optional props `isGeneratingReport?: boolean`, `reportAvailable?: boolean`, `onViewReport?: () => void`; renders `Loader2` spinner + "Generating your report…" text when `isGeneratingReport`; renders indigo "View Report" button with `FileText` icon when `reportAvailable`; default state (no evaluation) shows "Your conversation transcript has been saved." unchanged
- `src/components/agentspace/wizard/AgentConfigureView.tsx` — added `Tab = 'session' | 'evaluation'` type with tab pill row below header (`inline-flex bg-gray-100 rounded-lg p-1`, active tab `bg-white shadow-sm`); "Save Changes" button is only rendered when `activeTab === 'session'`; added `EvaluationTab` sub-component: criteria `<textarea>` with descriptive placeholder, "Generate with AI" button (calls `generateEvaluationCriteria(accessToken, {task_definition, users_raw_evaluation_criteria})`, `Sparkles` + `Loader2` icons); animated metrics preview card (metric tags in `indigo-50/indigo-100` pills + curator prompt text, `motion.div` fade-in on arrival); "Save Metrics" button calls `updateAgent(token, agentId, {transcript_evaluation_metrics: metrics})`; "Clear" link calls `updateAgent` with `transcript_evaluation_metrics: null`; empty dashed-border card when no metrics are configured; imported `generateEvaluationCriteria` from api
- `src/lib/api.ts` — added `transcript_evaluation_metrics?: EvaluationMetrics | null` to `updateAgent` updates parameter type

